# This repo's whole point is the .cursor/ framework, but Cursor dirs are often
# ignored globally. Re-include it here, then re-ignore the ADO config below.
!.cursor/

# Your filled-in ADO config holds your org / assignee details, so it stays out of
# git — `bash .cursor/dev/setup.sh` generates both from the tracked .example files.
# Everything else (your todo files) IS tracked: make your repo private if you want
# your list kept private.
.cursor/ado-config.md
.cursor/ado/target.md
